{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "While replicating such scenario data from real-world instances is nearly impossible due to the uncontrollability of actual scenes [9,56], customized scene simulation emerges as a vital and feasible alternative.",
    "It enables the precise modeling of specific conditions without high costs and logistical complexities of real-world data collection [4,76].To effectively simulate customized driving scenes, we identify three key properties as fundamental.",
    "First, the simulation should be capable of following sophisticated or abstract demands, thereby facilitating the production.",
    "Second, the simulation should generate photo-realistic, viewconsistent outcomes, which allow for the closest approximation to vehicle observations in real-world scenarios.",
    "Third, it should allow for the integration of external digital assets [6,48] with their photo-realistic textures and materials while fitting the lighting conditions."
  ],
